The decor of Dorlan's Tavern & Oyster Bar is authentic tavern style and outdoor seating is currently available during COVID-19.  The staff was nice and served everything quickly. The food options on the menu were limited. We had 2 dozens of oysters, shrimp nacho, fries, fried chicken tender and mozzarella sticks.  Overall, the food was decent but not outstandingly good. Our favorite was their oysters, which were fresh and flavorful with 3 different sauces. We didn't like their comfort food  and it definitely was overcooked, especially the fried chicken. It was dry and hard to chew.

Came into this spot to play pool with my brother, as it was recommended. I went to use the bathroom and there was a strong weed odor upon leaving the bathroom. When I re-approached the table, my brother said the the manager harassed him for smoking weed, that had become malodorous within the bar, and told him that this was “not a weed bar”. My brother doesn’t smoke or partake in drugs and told the manager such. I later asked the manager why he was singled out upon leaving the bathroom and he couldn’t give me an answer, other than that the bar “smelled the same way the last time he was here”. Again, my brother doesn’t smoke weed. AT ALL. We were singled out as the only brown people when we only wanted to play pool and no concrete answers were given as to why. This spot is located in the Seaport district of Manhattan which is pedestrian based, and anyone walking by can smell or smoke anyway they want, yet we were singled out. Not great.
